<p>I have a ListView with rows that use a customview.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt; &lt;derongan.upper.CheckedLinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" android:orientation="horizontal" android:layout_width="match_parent" android:layout_height="wrap_content"&gt;  &lt;EditText     android:id="@+id/edit_text"     android:layout_width="0dp"     android:layout_height="match_parent"     android:layout_weight="1"     android:hint="New Counter"     /&gt;  &lt;RadioButton     android:id="@+id/radio_button"     android:layout_width="wrap_content"     android:layout_height="match_parent"     android:clickable="false"     android:focusable="false"     android:focusableInTouchMode="false" /&gt; &lt;/derongan.upper.CheckedLinearLayout&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The CheckedLinearLayout implements checkable. When I click on a row in my ListView that has this layout, the radiobutton is not toggled but the EditText is selected. When I change the EditText to a TextView it behaves as expected. This leads me to believe the EditText is taking control of the Focus event and not allowing the parent view to change its checked state.</p>  <p>How do I fix this.</p>